message.content: The command 'ssh' is used to establish an encrypted connection between two computers, in this case the local computer and a server called 'ec2-34-221-131-108.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com'. The '-i "~/UserKey.pem"' option specifies the path to a private key file that will be used to authenticate the user on the remote server. The '-C' option is used to run commands on the remote server, and the '-L 25900:localhost:5900' option sets up a local port forwarding from the remote server to another server listening on port 5900. Finally, 'user@ec2-34-221-131-108.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com' specifies the username and hostname of the remote server.
